message.content:
An Irish Setter is a breed of dog that originated in Ireland.
They are typically medium to large in size with a muscular and athletic build.
Their coat is shiny and silky with feathering on the legs, tail, chest, and ears.
The coat color is a rich mahogany or chestnut with some white markings on the chest and feet.
Irish Setters are known for their friendly and outgoing personalities and are commonly used as hunting and family dogs.
They have long, floppy ears that add to their charm, and a long, tapered tail.
This breed is often seen in dog shows or as a beloved companion pets in households worldwide.
